<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1916-04-18T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1916-04-18T00:00:00-05:00" n="1225" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1225">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 811.142/1549b</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss>
                                    to the Chargé in Turkey</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_PH1" type="to"><hi rend="italic">Philip</hi></persName>)</head>
                            <opener>
                                <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                            </opener>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1916-04-18">
                                        <hi rend="italic">April 18, 1916</hi>
                                    </date>.</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>2332. Pay $50,000 Constantinople chapter American Red Cross for use
                                in cooperation with Red Crescent Society in providing relief
                                starving civilian population Constantinople, Smyrna, Brusa,
                                Adrianople, and other cities and communities of Turkey in Europe and
                                western part Turkey in Asia, from American Red Cross.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <persName corresp="#p_LR1">
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Lansing</hi>
                                    </persName>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>